	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "grub2: bypass the GRUB password protection feature (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2023-4001",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2023-4001",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: An authentication bypass flaw was found in GRUB due to the way that GRUB uses the UUID of a device to search for the configuration file that contains the password hash for the GRUB password protection feature. An attacker capable of attaching an external drive such as a USB stick containing a file system with a duplicate UUID (the same as in the \"/boot/\" file system) can bypass the GRUB password protection feature on UEFI systems, which enumerate removable drives before non-removable ones. This issue was introduced in a downstream patch in Red Hat's version of grub2 and does not affect the upstream package.",
